<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-11T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-11T23:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13533: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-12T12:00:00+08:00">June 12,
                                1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 12—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Substance of Nanking’s June 11, 9 a.m.,<note n="75" xml:id="d541fn75"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_202">p.
                                202</ref>.</note> and June 11, 11 a.m.,<note n="76" xml:id="d541fn76">Not printed.</note> is being communicated to Navy
                            to be forwarded to Admiral Allen. U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> will leave Hankow for Changsha morning of June
                            13th.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Department, Peiping and Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>